      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are correct that the core of nationalism is prioritizing one group, and that inherent prioritization is precisely what makes it a double-edged sword. The \"good\" version isn't a sanitized version of the \"bad\" one; it's a *disciplined* version where the in-group focus is channeled into positive collective action, like shared cultural preservation or civic duty. When that focus becomes exclusionary and hostile to outsiders, it crosses the line into dangerous chauvinism.",
